The paper deals with competitive analysis of algorithms in a distributed shared memory setting, which involves issues related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The specific problem studied is list accessing, which is a classic problem in algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also uses combinatorial techniques to prove bounds, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
